  "articleSummary": "Thearticle is a brief tutorial aimed at system administrators and MongoDB users who encounter the warning “/sys/kernel/mm/transparent_hugepage/defrag is ‘always’.” It explains that MongoDB recommends disabling Transparent Huge Pages (THP) to avoid performance degradation, and provides a ready‑to‑run set of commands for Debian/Ubuntu that download, install, and enable an init script to turn THP off at boot. The piece references the official MongoDB documentation for deeper context, positioning itself as a quick‑fix guide rather than a deep analysis. The tone is pragmatic and instructional, using a straightforward step‑by‑step format without metaphorical framing.",
